            "text_pkrhc9": {
              "type": "text",
              "settings": {
                "text": "<p>At Cala Falcó, sustainability means thinking long term and acting with care across the full system of what we do.<br/><br/>As an island-based project, we work in close relationship with limited and precious resources. Water is scarce, ecosystems are delicate, and every decision carries weight. For us, sustainability means using those resources responsibly, minimising harm, and making choices that support the long-term health of the land, the integrity of our processes, and the quality of what we create.<br/><br/>It also means recognising that sustainability is not perfection. It is a practice of continuous improvement. Learning, refining, and evolving over time.<br/><br/>In this way, sustainability becomes not a statement, but a discipline. One that asks us to work with greater responsibility, coherence, and care from land to product.</p>",
